s2.update(get_prefixes(num))\n        \n        # Find the longest common prefix\n        longest_common_prefix_length = 0\n        for prefix in prefixes1:\n            if prefix in prefixes2:\n                longest_common_prefix_length = max(longest_common_prefix_length, len(prefix))\n        \n        return longest_common_prefix_length\n```\n\nThis solution works by first generating all possible prefixes for each number in `arr1` and `arr2`. It then finds the longest common prefix by checking which prefixes from `arr1` are also present in `arr2`. The length of the longest common prefix is returned. If no common prefix exists, the function returns 0. This approach ensures that we efficiently find the longest common prefix among all pairs of integers from the two arrays.", "estimated_date": 1708214400000}